Parthib's Changes

Date and time: 2026-04-08 18:39:42 PDT

What changed:
- The live phone camera preview was changed from slow JPEG image snapshots to WebRTC live video.
- WebSocket is still used, but now only for signaling and coordination.
- The actual live camera video now goes directly from the phone browser to the dashboard browser through WebRTC.

Why this was changed:
- The old system sent repeated JPEG frames over WebSocket.
- That made the camera preview slow and laggy.
- WebRTC is designed for low-latency live video, so it should make the preview much smoother.

Main code changes:
- The server now relays WebRTC signaling messages between the phone and the dashboard.
- The phone now creates a WebRTC preview connection and sends its camera track through it.
- The dashboard now receives that live video track and shows it in the camera widget.
- The old image-based path was kept as a fallback and for recording support.

Simple before/after:
- Before: phone camera -> JPEG snapshots -> WebSocket -> server -> dashboard image refresh
- After: phone camera -> WebRTC live stream -> dashboard video

Files changed:
- fleet-server/index.js
- client-mobile/phone.js
- dashboard/dashboard.js
- dashboard/widgets.js
- dashboard/styles.css
